---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Melvin Hogan | About: Independent UX & AI Practice"
  description="How I work as an independent UX and AI consultant: websites, apps, and branding with clear strategy, practical AI in the workflow, and craft you can ship."
  ogTitle="Melvin Hogan | About: Independent UX & AI Practice"
  ogDescription="Websites, apps, and branding with a single coherent story. Practical AI where it earns its place, plus judgment and craft."
  twitterTitle="Melvin Hogan | About: Independent UX & AI Practice"
  twitterDescription="Websites, apps, and branding with a single coherent story. Practical AI where it earns its place, plus judgment and craft."
  current="bio"
  wfPageId="6890c3ab41aba347ed1dd348"
>
  <main id="main-content">
    <section data-w-id="3a5b15e1-80f4-6493-f60d-d1f9467d0913" style="opacity:0" class="sitetitle">
      <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer w-container">
        <h1 class="main-headline">
          About: UX, AI, websites,<br />apps & branding
        </h1>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="bio" aria-labelledby="bio-intro-heading">
      <h2 id="bio-intro-heading" class="sr-only">Overview</h2>
      <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer container-13 w-container">
        <img
          src="/assets/images/6827517d26402a8aa52628e8_profilebw.jpeg"
          loading="lazy"
          style="opacity:0"
          data-w-id="cb83ec68-f35d-b05b-019e-720dd7912812"
          alt=""
          class="profile"
        />
        <p data-w-id="cb83ec68-f35d-b05b-019e-720dd7912813" style="opacity:0" class="callout">
          I'm Melvin Hogan. I work as an <em>independent UX and AI consultant</em> with founders and teams, to create websites that tell a clear story, apps with flows people can follow,
          and branding that ties the whole experience together. With 20+ years in UX and product, I stay
          close to taste, judgment, and craft. I put AI in the workflow where it earns its place, to explore
          directions faster, draft and structure content, and pressure-test ideas before you sink build time, so you
          get less friction between "we should" and "we shipped it." One thread from brand to interface, so your
          site, your app, and your story feel like the same product.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="offerings" aria-labelledby="core-offerings-heading">
      <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer w-container">
        <h2 id="core-offerings-heading">What I focus on</h2>
        <p>
          Hands-on work across the three areas that show up on the home page, so vision and execution stay connected:
        </p>
        <ul role="list" class="workflow">
          <li class="coreofferings">
            Websites & digital presence<br />Structure, narrative, and UX so your site converts attention into trust
            and reflects how you actually work.<br />‍
          </li>
          <li class="coreofferings">
            Apps & product UX<br />Flows, information architecture, and interface clarity for web and mobile, so your
            product feels obvious to the people who rely on it.<br />‍
          </li>
          <li class="coreofferings">
            Branding & story<br />Voice, visual direction, and consistency across touchpoints, so your brand reads as
            intentional, not improvised.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section aria-labelledby="transformation-heading">
      <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer w-container">
        <h2 id="transformation-heading">What tends to change</h2>
        <ul role="list">
          <li>A clearer story on the site and fewer gaps between what you say and what people experience.</li>
          <li>Product flows and language that line up, so the app matches the promise.</li>
          <li>AI used for speed and iteration in the workflow, not as a substitute for judgment.</li>
          <li>Design and delivery that feel like one thread from brand to interface.</li>
          <li class="list-item-5">
            Less back-and-forth between teams and a faster path from decision to something you can ship.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="contact" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <div id="contact" class="w-layout-blockcontainer contact w-container">
        <h2 id="contact-heading" class="sr-only">Book a consultation</h2>
        <a
          href="https://app.usemotion.com/meet/mel-hogan/cultureeval"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="contactbutton w-button"
        >
          Book a free 30-minute call
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
